The key insight is: from `split_epi f` we get `g` with `f ≫ g = id X`. Since `f` is then epi (via `retraction_epi`), and we can show `f ≫ (g ≫ f) = f ≫ id Y`, we can cancel `f` on the left to get `g ≫ f = id Y`.

```lean
theorem Category.iso_of_mono_and_split_epi {X Y : α} (f : Hom X Y)
    (hm : Mono f) (he : split_epi f) : IsIso f := by
  obtain ⟨g, hfg⟩ := he
  have hf_epi : Epi f := retraction_epi f g hfg
  have hgf : g ≫ f = id Y := by
    apply hf_epi
    rw [← assoc, hfg, id_comp, comp_id]
  exact ⟨g, hfg, hgf⟩
```
